  "response": "Okay, to give you the best recommendations, I need a little more information about what you like!  But, I can give you a broad selection based on popular and critically acclaimed songs across different genres:\n\n**If you want something POPULAR and TIMELESS:**\n\n*   **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" - Queen:**  A classic for a reason.  Operatic, rock, and just plain epic.\n*   **\"Like a Rolling Stone\" - Bob Dylan:** A cornerstone of rock and roll, with powerful lyrics and a revolutionary sound.\n*   **\"Billie Jean\" - Michael Jackson:**  Infectious beat, iconic vocals, and a legendary music video.\n*   **\"Imagine\" - John Lennon:**  A beautiful and hopeful anthem for peace.\n*   **\"Hey Jude\" - The Beatles:** Uplifting and unforgettable.\n\n**If you want something more CONTEMPORARY POP:**\n\n*   **\"Blinding Lights\" - The Weeknd:** An 80s-inspired synth-pop banger.\n*   **\"As It Was\" - Harry Styles:** Catchy and melancholic pop perfection.\n*   **\"drivers license\" - Olivia Rodrigo:** A heartbreak anthem for the modern age.\n*   **\"Bad Habits\" - Ed Sheeran:** Uplifting and catchy\n*   **\"Levitating\" - Dua Lipa:** Fun, danceable, and full of energy.\n\n**If you're in a ROCK mood:**\n\n*   **\"Stairway to Heaven\" - Led Zeppelin:**  A legendary epic with a gradual build-up.\n*   **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" - Nirvana:**  The anthem of a generation.\n*   **\"Enter Sandman\" - Metallica:** A heavy metal masterpiece.\n*   **\"Sweet Child o' Mine\" - Guns N' Roses:**  A classic rock ballad with an iconic guitar riff.\n*   **\"Seven Nation Army\" - The White Stripes:** A simple but incredibly effective riff-driven song.\n\n**If you want some HIP-HOP/RAP:**\n\n*   **\"Alright\" - Kendrick Lamar:** A powerful and uplifting anthem of resilience.\n*   **\"Juicy\" - The Notorious B.I.G.:**  A classic rags-to-riches story.\n*   **\"Lose Yourself\" - Eminem:**  Intense, motivational, and technically brilliant.\n*   **\"Empire State of Mind\" - Jay-Z ft. Alicia Keys:** A celebration of New York City.\n*   **\"Ms. Jackson\" - Outkast:** Funky, soulful, and incredibly catchy.\n\n**If you want something SOULFUL/R&B:**\n\n*   **\"What's Going On\" - Marvin Gaye:**  A socially conscious and timeless masterpiece.\n*   **\"Respect\" - Aretha Franklin:**  A powerful and empowering anthem.\n*   **\"At Last\" - Etta James:**  A classic love song with incredible vocals.\n*   **\"A Change Is Gonna Come\" - Sam Cooke:**  A hopeful and moving civil rights anthem.\n*   **\"Killing Me Softly With His Song\" - Roberta Flack:** Soulful and melodic classic.\n\n**If you want some INDIE/ALTERNATIVE:**\n\n*   **\"Where Is My Mind?\" - Pixies:**  A quiet-loud masterpiece.\n*   **\"The Less I Know The Better\" - Tame Impala:** Psychedelic, funky, and catchy.\n*   **\"Mr. Brightside\" - The Killers:**  An indie rock anthem that everyone seems to know.\n*   **\"Somebody That I Used to Know\" - Gotye ft. Kimbra:**  Unique, layered, and emotionally resonant.\n*   **\"Little Talks\" - Of Monsters and Men:** Uplifting and folk-inspired.\n\n**If you want something a little different:**\n\n*   **\"Hallelujah\" - Leonard Cohen:**  A haunting and beautiful song with many interpretations.\n*   **\"Nuvole Bianche\" - Ludovico Einaudi:**  Beautiful piano\n*   **\"Clair de Lune\" - Claude Debussy:** Beautiful, classic music.\n\nTo give you the **BEST** recommendations, tell me:\n\n*   **What genres do you usually listen to?** (Pop, Rock, Hip-Hop, R&B, Country, Electronic, Classical, etc.)\n*   **Who are some of your favorite artists?**\n*   **What kind of mood are you in?** (Happy, sad, energetic, relaxed, etc.)\n\nThe more I know, the better my suggestions will be!\n",
